# Flathub curation ALLOWLIST — force-include an app id even if it fails one of
# the automatic filters (license / verification / sandbox permissions / OARS
# content rating) in svk-flathub-sync.py. One app id per line; '#' starts a
# comment; blank lines ignored. Same flat-file shape as /etc/svk/flatpaks.list.
#
# This is the EXAMPLE seeded to /var/lib/svk/flathub-allowlist on first run
# (see svk-flathub-sync.py: seed_list()) — edit the real file on the server,
# not this one; it does not get overwritten once it exists.
#
# If an id appears on BOTH this list and flathub-blocklist, the blocklist wins
# and the sync script warns loudly about it.
#
# org.example.TrustedButUnverifiedApp
